<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key D (2 sharps: F#, C#). Trinitarian hymn, 10 bars. "33" triads and "43" inversions.
- Bb (non-diatonic) in bars 7 → Em (②m) - chromatic mediant handled diatonically.
- Bm7 = ③m, F#m = ⑥m, Em = ②m. A7 = ⑤7. G = ④.
- LH 4-note open voicings throughout. RH 2-note thirds.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 6 LH moves from Bm to G (③m→④): inner voice B3-B3 held as common tone.
- Bars 7-8 LH stepwise: G → Em, providing smooth bass descent G-E.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opens with D-A call-response. Bar 6 peak (d5-F#5 RH). Final D cadence bar 10.
- Bars 3-4 have melodic rests on beat 1 — harp fills the silence with sustained chord.
-->
